Freudian Slip The term is popularly used today in a humorous way when a person makes a mistake in speech. In these situations, observers often suggest (in a comic way) that the mistake reveals some type of hidden emotion on the part of the speaker.
I got this February 1st, a good reward after learning to steelhead all winter. My best steelhead yet. Thats a monster l2p!
